WEBVTT

00:00.102 --> 00:02.772
<i>[low ambient music]</i>

00:02.806 --> 00:08.170
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:08.266 --> 00:11.264
<i>"There once was a serpent...</i>

00:11.768 --> 00:14.334
"who only traveled one direction:

00:14.443 --> 00:17.407
always forward, never backward."

00:17.440 --> 00:18.843
<i>[soft piano music]</i>

00:18.876 --> 00:20.623
<i>"Until one day,</i>

00:20.777 --> 00:23.614
<i>the serpent came upon a demon."</i>

00:23.647 --> 00:27.417
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:27.451 --> 00:29.820
"The demon cursed the serpent,

00:29.914 --> 00:31.649
<i>"driving him insane,</i>

00:31.756 --> 00:34.799
<i>causing him to eat his own tail."</i>

00:34.859 --> 00:36.960
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:36.985 --> 00:39.612
<i>"The serpent was blind,</i>

00:39.748 --> 00:43.493
<i>"but a few, those who were serious,</i>

00:43.632 --> 00:46.608
<i>"knew the serpent's true path,</i>

00:46.936 --> 00:49.906
"so they created a weapon,

00:50.233 --> 00:52.777
<i>a weapon to destroy the demon."</i>

00:52.810 --> 00:55.847
<i>[music swells]</i>

00:55.880 --> 00:57.782
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:57.814 --> 01:00.651
<i>[low ambient music]</i>

01:00.684 --> 01:02.753
[echoing crack]

01:02.786 --> 01:05.922
[light splatting]

01:05.955 --> 01:09.460
[panting]

01:09.493 --> 01:11.062
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:11.095 --> 01:13.106
Ticky-tock...

01:13.910 --> 01:15.482
those eyes...

01:15.565 --> 01:19.437
left, right, swaying
like a granddaddy clock.

01:19.470 --> 01:20.672
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:20.705 --> 01:23.408
Jennifer, where have you been?

01:23.440 --> 01:25.042
- [groans]
- Whoa, whoa...

01:25.076 --> 01:27.544
Whoa, hey-hey-hey. Cole!

01:27.577 --> 01:29.913
Hey, Jennifer, hey, stay with me.

01:29.946 --> 01:32.817
- Jennifer...
- Ms. Goines, what happened?

01:32.850 --> 01:34.952
It was all in here...

01:34.985 --> 01:36.387
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:36.419 --> 01:38.455
Now it's all in there.

01:38.488 --> 01:40.524
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:40.557 --> 01:42.814
Told you, Otter Eyes.

01:42.892 --> 01:44.221
If you gave me yellow...

01:44.260 --> 01:45.769
I could paint you the world!

01:45.795 --> 01:47.699
<i>[voice echoes]</i>

01:47.732 --> 01:53.705
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:53.738 --> 01:55.979
Oh, my God.

01:56.539 --> 01:58.508
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

01:58.541 --> 02:00.911
What the hell is this?

02:00.945 --> 02:04.716
Some kind of Primary message?

02:04.748 --> 02:09.014
The Primaries had ample time
to say what they mean.

02:09.485 --> 02:11.455
This isn't a message.

02:11.488 --> 02:14.524
<i>[low ambient music]</i>

02:14.558 --> 02:18.129
They've given us
one final mystery to solve.

02:18.161 --> 02:21.131
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

02:21.165 --> 02:28.540
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:33.086 --> 02:36.275
<font color="#0080ff">Synced & corrected by</font> kinglouisxx
<font color="#0080ff">www.</font>addic7ed<font color="#0080ff">.com</font>

02:47.857 --> 02:49.660
Deacon's?

02:54.498 --> 02:56.667
I miss him.

02:59.069 --> 03:00.872
So do I.

03:05.943 --> 03:07.812
I cleaned the wounds,

03:08.007 --> 03:09.776
but they're just gonna hurt
for a little while.

03:09.801 --> 03:12.379
I'm sorry, there isn't
much more I could do.

03:12.550 --> 03:14.919
<i>[low ambient music]</i>

03:14.960 --> 03:17.663
You're a good doctor, Cassie.

03:17.688 --> 03:20.458
[mumbles, clears throat]

03:20.491 --> 03:22.993
[grunting]

03:23.027 --> 03:24.928
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:24.970 --> 03:26.459
The symbols...

03:26.484 --> 03:28.533
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:28.565 --> 03:31.169
What do they mean?
What are we looking for?

03:31.201 --> 03:36.540
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:36.574 --> 03:38.176
The center.

03:38.208 --> 03:42.813
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:43.079 --> 03:46.115
54 unique symbols, by my count,

03:46.140 --> 03:47.784
in no apparent order.

03:47.818 --> 03:51.755
The various strands and pieces
don't even align,

03:51.789 --> 03:54.091
so there's no telling the logic.

03:54.123 --> 03:56.226
Far too many to be numeric;

03:56.260 --> 03:58.863
twice too many to be alphabetical.

03:58.896 --> 04:01.466
There doesn't appear to be a pattern.

04:01.498 --> 04:03.099
<i>It's completely random.</i>

04:03.133 --> 04:06.103
<i>[tense music]</i>

04:06.135 --> 04:13.510
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:15.945 --> 04:19.082
[footsteps running, approaching]

04:19.116 --> 04:20.584
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:20.618 --> 04:22.854
We're looking at them
from the wrong angle.

04:22.887 --> 04:24.154
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:24.188 --> 04:26.491
Start at the center.

04:26.524 --> 04:28.092
It's a spiral.

04:28.125 --> 04:30.127
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:30.159 --> 04:32.662
They're puzzle pieces.

04:33.731 --> 04:35.533
They fit together.

04:35.565 --> 04:37.267
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:37.301 --> 04:38.603
[keyboard clacking]

04:38.635 --> 04:39.803
Ten macro-symbols,

04:39.837 --> 04:41.539
representing zero through nine.

04:41.717 --> 04:44.654
Presented in a logarithmic spiral.

04:44.679 --> 04:46.676
<i>[slow, solemn string music]</i>

04:46.710 --> 04:49.613
This is a program for a machine.

04:49.647 --> 04:51.548
There seems to be a pattern

04:51.582 --> 04:54.302
of two symbols repeating
in groups of four.

04:54.327 --> 04:55.620
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:55.652 --> 04:56.987
These are dates.

04:57.012 --> 04:59.208
With which of these
are we most familiar?

04:59.233 --> 05:00.930
1-9 and 2-0:

05:01.024 --> 05:03.820
the 1900s and the 2000s.

05:04.263 --> 05:07.566
Given four numbers, I should
be able to decipher the rest.

05:07.742 --> 05:11.059
The Primaries built
a machine for you, Mr. Cole.

05:11.452 --> 05:13.188
Perhaps this can tell us

05:13.230 --> 05:15.673
where it was meant to send you.

05:15.705 --> 05:18.141
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:18.174 --> 05:21.177
<i>[dark tones, high-pitched ringing]</i>

05:21.210 --> 05:24.181
[distant siren wailing]

05:24.214 --> 05:28.019
<i>[tense music]</i>

05:28.051 --> 05:31.352
Get dressed, Marion.
We have to stay on the move,

05:31.448 --> 05:33.805
find a way back to my mother.

05:33.977 --> 05:35.819
We should drive down to Raritan.

05:35.919 --> 05:38.756
Katerina and Elliot clearly know you.

05:41.198 --> 05:44.568
- Hey, Marion, this is...
- My name is Emma.

05:45.936 --> 05:50.073
Marion is just a name I made up...

05:50.106 --> 05:52.342
<i>[solemn string music]</i>

05:52.375 --> 05:55.947
The name that I chose for myself.

05:55.979 --> 05:59.683
It was the first choice I ever made.

06:00.059 --> 06:01.693
Now you can choose to help us.

06:01.718 --> 06:03.988
You cannot stop what never began.

06:04.515 --> 06:07.852
Not you, not Katerina, not James Cole.

06:07.877 --> 06:08.992
Your son.

06:09.025 --> 06:12.162
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:12.512 --> 06:14.015
It may begin and end with her,

06:14.040 --> 06:17.076
but somehow in the middle
is you and him.

06:17.108 --> 06:19.344
That's impossible.

06:19.554 --> 06:21.598
- No, I haven't had a child.
- You will.

06:21.623 --> 06:24.317
That's why I was sent here, to find you,

06:24.350 --> 06:26.486
to find out how James's mother
knew the legend,

06:26.519 --> 06:28.321
and now I know.

06:28.353 --> 06:30.689
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:30.723 --> 06:33.225
<i>[echoing] What's it mean?</i>

06:33.259 --> 06:35.810
<i>[echoing] I don't know.</i>

06:36.194 --> 06:38.356
<i>I didn't write it.</i>

06:38.531 --> 06:41.934
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:41.968 --> 06:44.212
Who did?

06:44.470 --> 06:46.339
[sighs]

06:46.372 --> 06:47.674
<i>Your mother.</i>

06:47.706 --> 06:49.308
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:49.341 --> 06:52.044
You're not meant
to destroy the world, Marion.

06:52.078 --> 06:54.480
You're meant to help save it.

06:54.512 --> 06:56.448
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:56.482 --> 06:59.519
[crickets chirping]

07:03.254 --> 07:05.725
What if Katerina and Elliot
don't believe us?

07:05.757 --> 07:07.960
I'm their daughter.

07:07.994 --> 07:09.429
DNA...

07:09.461 --> 07:12.031
- Yeah, we can prove it.
- Yeah.

07:13.031 --> 07:14.366
I'm going to be a mother.

07:14.399 --> 07:16.201
[laughs]

07:16.235 --> 07:17.437
- [car crashes]
- Oh!

07:17.470 --> 07:19.739
[tires screeching, engine revving]

07:19.771 --> 07:22.074
[gasps] They found us!

07:22.107 --> 07:24.444
[gunshots]

07:24.477 --> 07:26.512
Hold on!

07:26.545 --> 07:29.749
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

07:29.781 --> 07:31.116
[gasps, grunts]

07:31.149 --> 07:33.418
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:33.451 --> 07:36.755
[engine revving]

07:36.788 --> 07:38.523
- [car bangs]
- [gasping]

07:38.557 --> 07:40.492
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:40.526 --> 07:42.160
[engine revving]

07:42.194 --> 07:44.497
- [grunts]
- [gasps]

07:44.530 --> 07:45.565
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:45.598 --> 07:47.499
[car crashes, items clatter]

07:47.533 --> 07:49.102
<i>[low ambient music]</i>

07:49.134 --> 07:50.402
Within the Primary code,

07:50.435 --> 07:53.105
we found dozens of temporal coordinates,

07:53.139 --> 07:55.273
more specifically, our coordinates.

07:55.307 --> 07:58.711
2013, then 2015: Philadelphia.

07:58.744 --> 08:00.313
1987: Tokyo.

08:00.345 --> 08:03.803
'44, '75, 1491, and so on.

08:03.850 --> 08:06.519
Everywhere, every-when you've ever been.

08:06.552 --> 08:08.054
Except one.

08:08.086 --> 08:09.688
A set of coordinates which doesn't match

08:09.721 --> 08:11.656
anything in our system.

08:11.689 --> 08:14.694
April 3rd, 2018:

08:14.727 --> 08:16.562
New York, JFK Airport.

08:16.595 --> 08:18.264
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:18.297 --> 08:20.732
That's two days before...

08:20.766 --> 08:22.480
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:22.505 --> 08:24.541
The plague.

08:24.703 --> 08:26.773
<i>[music swells]</i>

08:26.806 --> 08:28.807
<i>[low, tense music]</i>

08:28.841 --> 08:31.210
Our first mission.

08:31.243 --> 08:33.046
The best weapon to kill Olivia?

08:33.078 --> 08:34.479
Destroy the one that made her.

08:34.513 --> 08:36.282
The first reported cases of the virus

08:36.315 --> 08:38.150
were global and simultaneous...

08:38.183 --> 08:40.552
Argentina, London, Prague...

08:40.586 --> 08:44.190
New York, on the 5th and 6th of April.

08:44.222 --> 08:45.724
Why two days before?

08:45.758 --> 08:49.023
The plague has an incubation
period of 24 to 48 hours.

08:49.048 --> 08:51.096
You can't survive it.

08:51.129 --> 08:52.498
You can only spread it.

08:52.530 --> 08:56.028
And in 36 hours,
the world will realize...

08:56.101 --> 08:58.059
it's over.

08:58.104 --> 09:00.306
And JFK is one of the most traveled

09:00.331 --> 09:02.985
international airports in North America.

09:03.442 --> 09:05.212
This time...

09:05.610 --> 09:07.145
this place...

09:07.178 --> 09:09.686
Is when they release the plague.

09:10.316 --> 09:12.451
<i>[intense percussive music]</i>

09:21.659 --> 09:24.150
Initiate splinter sequence.

09:24.395 --> 09:27.532
[machine whirring, accelerates]

09:27.566 --> 09:31.269
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:31.302 --> 09:34.273
<i>[soft, high-pitched ringing]</i>

09:34.306 --> 09:36.509
<i>[aery ambience]</i>

09:36.542 --> 09:38.211
[heavy breathing]

09:38.244 --> 09:40.547
[screaming]

09:43.317 --> 09:46.325
[echoing] Officer down! Officer down!

09:46.458 --> 09:49.266
We have an active shooter:
Terminal One concourse.

09:49.321 --> 09:50.897
Officer down!

09:50.922 --> 09:52.390
<i>[ominous tone]</i>

09:52.423 --> 09:55.227
<i>[tense, pulsating percussive music]</i>

09:55.260 --> 09:56.761
<i>[ominous tone]</i>

09:56.794 --> 09:59.764
<i>[tense music]</i>

09:59.797 --> 10:01.333
Cole!

10:01.366 --> 10:02.634
- The virus!
- [grunts]

10:02.668 --> 10:03.836
[siren wailing]

10:03.869 --> 10:05.638
[glass shatters]

10:05.671 --> 10:09.199
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

10:09.366 --> 10:11.269
Behind you!

10:11.543 --> 10:13.312
<i>[dramatic tone]</i>

10:13.345 --> 10:16.883
<i>[tense music]</i>

10:16.916 --> 10:18.751
We need to restart.

10:18.783 --> 10:21.754
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

10:21.787 --> 10:27.427
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:31.963 --> 10:34.498
<i>[low ambient music]</i>

10:34.782 --> 10:36.785
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:37.932 --> 10:41.102
It's definitely M5-10.

10:41.135 --> 10:42.870
We never knew how it was released.

10:42.903 --> 10:44.002
We do now.

10:44.027 --> 10:46.263
If they only had one remaining sample.

10:46.340 --> 10:49.566
Well, then this is how
you maximize its impact:

10:49.643 --> 10:52.046
turn a building full of innocent people

10:52.079 --> 10:54.181
into traveling time bombs.

10:54.214 --> 10:55.316
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:55.349 --> 10:59.286
[siren wailing, people clamoring]

10:59.318 --> 11:00.887
<i>[dramatic tone]</i>

11:00.921 --> 11:02.323
So what now?

11:02.355 --> 11:04.758
Go back and stop the tall man
from dropping it?

11:04.791 --> 11:08.861
Or... steal it out from under him
before he can.

11:08.894 --> 11:10.930
One guess where they've been keeping it.

11:10.964 --> 11:12.299
<i>[music swells]</i>

11:12.331 --> 11:13.967
<i>[dark tones]</i>

11:14.000 --> 11:17.270
<i>[high-pitched ringing]</i>

11:17.303 --> 11:18.404
[crickets chirping]

11:18.438 --> 11:21.207
After Jennifer vanished,
the whole business collapsed.

11:21.240 --> 11:23.811
Scrapped and sold off for parts.

11:23.844 --> 11:25.845
That'll happen when your CEO promises

11:25.879 --> 11:28.641
to genetically engineer a unicorn.

11:28.782 --> 11:30.555
The plague,

11:30.850 --> 11:32.524
another Markridge facility.

11:32.578 --> 11:35.322
It's too easy. Something's off.

11:35.355 --> 11:37.291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:37.323 --> 11:38.691
Come on.

11:38.725 --> 11:45.899
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:47.768 --> 11:49.842
This feel familiar to you?

11:50.403 --> 11:52.521
The Night Room.

11:52.839 --> 11:54.708
[sparks buzzing]

11:54.740 --> 11:57.711
[echoing laughter]

11:57.744 --> 12:00.714
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:00.746 --> 12:03.216
[mechanical hissing]

12:03.249 --> 12:05.028
<i>[echoing] What is that thing?</i>

12:05.118 --> 12:07.005
<i>[echoing] The origin.</i>

12:07.086 --> 12:11.215
<i>...inside that'll make
a centuries-old virus.</i>

12:11.291 --> 12:13.260
There's something about its eyes.

12:13.285 --> 12:15.188
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:15.228 --> 12:17.067
<i>[echoing] It's eyes...</i>

12:17.129 --> 12:20.266
<i>[low ambient music]</i>

12:20.299 --> 12:22.869
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:22.903 --> 12:24.738
I think that's us.

12:24.770 --> 12:26.906
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:26.940 --> 12:29.910
<i>[eerie, ominous chords]</i>

12:29.942 --> 12:37.150
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:44.609 --> 12:46.178
Power's still on.

12:46.226 --> 12:47.529
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:47.554 --> 12:49.189
Cold storage.

12:49.730 --> 12:52.700
<i>[music builds]</i>

12:52.733 --> 12:53.934
[electronic beep]

12:53.966 --> 12:56.937
[door clicks, mechanical hissing]

12:56.970 --> 13:00.740
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:00.773 --> 13:03.744
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

13:03.777 --> 13:08.215
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:08.248 --> 13:11.051
That's it, the one from the airport.

13:11.084 --> 13:13.720
[exhales] Now we just
need to destroy it.

13:13.754 --> 13:15.089
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:16.456 --> 13:18.024
<i>- [elevator dings]
- I just don't wanna</i>

13:18.049 --> 13:20.664
accidentally release the damn thing
in a hotel in Midtown.

13:20.689 --> 13:23.003
Well, viruses need
specific conditions to thrive.

13:23.028 --> 13:24.197
They take time to die.

13:24.229 --> 13:25.492
We burned it last time,

13:25.531 --> 13:28.134
but since you don't want
to set the hotel on fire,

13:28.167 --> 13:30.169
we'll drown it.

13:30.202 --> 13:31.804
<i>[ominous tone]</i>

13:31.837 --> 13:33.206
[gun clicks]

13:33.239 --> 13:36.876
<i>[eerie, ominous chords]</i>

13:36.909 --> 13:39.846
<i>[low ambient music]</i>

13:39.879 --> 13:42.115
Hannah?

13:42.148 --> 13:43.534
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:43.559 --> 13:45.753
<i>You've been stranded here for years.</i>

13:45.786 --> 13:47.321
Why didn't you find us sooner?

13:47.354 --> 13:50.290
And risk it all? Causality?

13:50.322 --> 13:53.526
Accidentally undo something
that shouldn't be undone?

13:53.560 --> 13:56.694
I couldn't, so I waited.

13:57.129 --> 13:58.999
What happened?

13:59.032 --> 14:02.168
<i>[prolonged car honk]</i>

14:02.201 --> 14:05.172
<i>[eerie music]</i>

14:05.205 --> 14:06.540
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:06.572 --> 14:08.007
[horn stops]

14:08.041 --> 14:10.844
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:10.877 --> 14:13.847
[engine revs, tires screech]

14:13.879 --> 14:16.115
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

14:16.148 --> 14:18.217
[door clicks, opens]

14:18.250 --> 14:22.188
<i>[tense percussive music]</i>

14:22.221 --> 14:23.890
[door thuds closed]

14:23.923 --> 14:27.393
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:27.427 --> 14:30.129
- We gotta go. Come on.
- [groans]

14:30.163 --> 14:31.831
- Come on.
- [groans sharply]

14:31.864 --> 14:33.399
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

14:33.432 --> 14:37.303
[gunshots]

14:42.142 --> 14:43.844
[insects chirping and buzzing]

14:43.877 --> 14:46.513
[both panting]

14:46.546 --> 14:48.449
Okay...

14:52.934 --> 14:55.337
Hello? Help!

14:55.437 --> 14:57.054
Somebody's hurt!

14:57.123 --> 14:59.093
Hello?

15:00.527 --> 15:03.263
<i>[dramatic tone]</i>

15:03.296 --> 15:05.432
Jones sent you to find my mother?

15:05.465 --> 15:12.206
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:12.239 --> 15:14.408
Hey, hey, what's going on?

15:14.441 --> 15:16.576
- What happened to you?
- No, it was not me.

15:16.610 --> 15:19.513
The car crashed, um,
the man was shooting, then...

15:19.546 --> 15:22.249
- It's okay. It's okay.
- Please.

15:22.282 --> 15:23.850
It's... it's all right.

15:23.884 --> 15:26.759
<i>[soft piano music]</i>

15:26.784 --> 15:27.860
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:27.885 --> 15:30.521
Marion was the name she chose.

15:30.923 --> 15:32.803
Before that, there was Emma.

15:33.259 --> 15:35.028
She was from Titan.

15:35.061 --> 15:38.532
<i>[ominous music]</i>

15:38.565 --> 15:41.602
[electrical blasts]

15:44.270 --> 15:45.938
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:45.971 --> 15:48.607
<i>She was born with a single purpose...</i>

15:48.674 --> 15:51.143
<i>[slow, intense percussive music]</i>

15:51.177 --> 15:52.646
<i>To complete Titan</i>

15:52.678 --> 15:56.078
<i>so that it could initiate
one final sequence,</i>

15:56.164 --> 15:58.312
<i>something that my father called</i>

15:58.384 --> 16:01.140
<i>the Hartle Hawking State:</i>

16:01.220 --> 16:02.595
<i>space...</i>

16:02.794 --> 16:04.619
<i>without time,</i>

16:04.962 --> 16:06.963
<i>their Red Forest.</i>

16:07.192 --> 16:10.096
[machine droning]

16:10.129 --> 16:13.100
[rumbling, whirring]

16:13.133 --> 16:16.036
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:16.068 --> 16:19.838
<i>Titan will create
a paradox of time itself,</i>

16:20.005 --> 16:21.408
<i>moments over moments,</i>

16:21.441 --> 16:23.911
<i>so great that it could never be undone.</i>

16:23.943 --> 16:26.913
[towers whirring, droning]

16:26.946 --> 16:28.547
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:28.581 --> 16:32.018
Its effects will be felt across
every hour, every minute,

16:32.052 --> 16:34.528
every second simultaneously.

16:34.932 --> 16:37.182
<i>Every day that ever existed</i>

16:38.627 --> 16:41.272
<i>will be the last day on earth.</i>

16:41.393 --> 16:44.264
[alarm chiming]

16:44.297 --> 16:46.033
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:46.066 --> 16:48.191
Ms. Goines?

16:48.969 --> 16:50.537
Doomsday alarm woke me up.

16:50.570 --> 16:53.507
The readings from Titan
are unprecedented.

16:53.539 --> 16:57.143
The sheer volume of
temporal energy is astounding.

16:57.177 --> 16:58.544
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:58.578 --> 17:00.347
My mother once said that time travel

17:00.379 --> 17:03.516
was both the cause and
the effect of all of this.

17:03.550 --> 17:06.286
But none of that matters anymore.

17:06.319 --> 17:08.021
We have the virus.

17:08.053 --> 17:10.556
The Primaries sent us
here to destroy it.

17:10.589 --> 17:12.023
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:12.058 --> 17:14.227
<i>Once Olivia turns on her weapon,</i>

17:14.260 --> 17:16.163
<i>begins her Red Forest,</i>

17:16.195 --> 17:18.868
she'll exist outside of causality.

17:19.299 --> 17:22.243
Destroying the plague won't stop her.

17:22.569 --> 17:24.704
But it will rob us of the only weapon

17:24.737 --> 17:27.205
we have to use against her...

17:27.240 --> 17:29.009
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17:29.042 --> 17:31.110
<i>Time travel.</i>

17:31.144 --> 17:32.746
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:32.779 --> 17:36.049
The Primaries didn't send us
here to stop the plague.

17:36.081 --> 17:39.052
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:39.084 --> 17:40.936
They sent us here to release it.

17:40.961 --> 17:45.834
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:48.938 --> 17:51.726
No. No, no!

17:51.760 --> 17:55.266
This whole mission has been
about saving 7 billion people,

17:55.325 --> 17:57.305
not killing them.

17:58.083 --> 18:00.401
You can't ask me to do this.

18:00.817 --> 18:02.752
For what?

18:02.839 --> 18:05.976
Either 7 billion people die today...

18:07.478 --> 18:10.448
Or everyone dies forever.

18:10.480 --> 18:13.451
<i>[gentle orchestral music]</i>

18:13.483 --> 18:15.452
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:15.486 --> 18:18.422
<i>[record crackling]</i>

18:18.454 --> 18:21.424
[machine whirring]

18:21.458 --> 18:24.428
<i>[women singing in foreign language]</i>

18:24.460 --> 18:26.197
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:26.229 --> 18:27.999
[audio rewinds]

18:28.024 --> 18:30.084
<i>James Cole.</i>

18:30.819 --> 18:32.436
- [explosion]
- [yells]

18:32.469 --> 18:34.071
James Cole.

18:34.104 --> 18:35.472
<i>[voice echoes]</i>

18:35.506 --> 18:37.441
<i>Why do they know him?</i>

18:37.473 --> 18:38.549
[audio rewinds]

18:38.574 --> 18:40.924
The only one of true importance

18:40.976 --> 18:42.667
is James Cole!

18:42.730 --> 18:43.901
<i>Why?</i>

18:44.104 --> 18:46.574
[audio rewinds]

18:46.951 --> 18:49.487
[pattering]

18:49.519 --> 18:51.489
<i>You shouldn't be here.</i>

18:51.521 --> 18:53.356
<i>You have work to finish.</i>

18:53.390 --> 18:55.193
<i>[voice echoes]</i>

18:55.218 --> 18:57.452
The virus was taken
by James and Cassandra

18:57.493 --> 18:58.943
on the eve of its release.

18:59.006 --> 19:00.975
They've interfered again.

19:01.008 --> 19:03.377
Broken yet another cycle.

19:03.411 --> 19:08.191
<i>James Cole somehow remains
a threat to our perfect realm.</i>

19:08.249 --> 19:11.219
<i>Today, I will end his cycle,</i>

19:11.251 --> 19:12.453
<i>and then...</i>

19:12.487 --> 19:14.255
I will ensure the plague is born

19:14.288 --> 19:16.516
not as you may have intended,

19:17.090 --> 19:19.266
but as it always has.

19:20.094 --> 19:22.610
The Witness has spoken.

19:22.963 --> 19:25.767
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:29.837 --> 19:32.006
<i>Mothers die for their children.</i>

19:32.039 --> 19:34.776
Yours died protecting you.

19:35.976 --> 19:37.893
What was she like?

19:38.078 --> 19:39.900
Lost, I think.

19:40.781 --> 19:43.682
<i>She always said she felt
trapped between two worlds,</i>

19:43.785 --> 19:47.221
<i>the one she was raised in and this one,</i>

19:47.387 --> 19:49.289
the world she came to know.

19:49.322 --> 19:50.758
<i>[soft ambient music]</i>

19:50.791 --> 19:52.961
She grew up without her mother.

19:52.993 --> 19:54.795
Never knew her father.

19:54.828 --> 19:57.354
I don't think she realized
how much that it shaped her,

19:57.385 --> 20:00.167
until she was faced with
the idea of giving you up.

20:00.201 --> 20:03.238
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:03.270 --> 20:05.878
So she left,

20:06.014 --> 20:07.362
handed me off to my dad

20:07.417 --> 20:10.299
with nothing but that bullshit story.

20:10.845 --> 20:12.313
No.

20:12.346 --> 20:14.449
The story's not over yet, James.

20:14.481 --> 20:17.452
<i>[slow, purposeful string music]</i>

20:17.484 --> 20:20.053
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:20.087 --> 20:21.321
We should go.

20:21.355 --> 20:28.530
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:38.472 --> 20:40.808
Go home.

20:40.841 --> 20:42.476
[door clicks open]

20:42.510 --> 20:48.116
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:48.148 --> 20:49.516
[door closes]

20:49.549 --> 20:51.385
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:51.418 --> 20:52.920
<i>You sent them where?</i>

20:52.953 --> 20:56.023
We found the coordinates in your code:

20:56.057 --> 20:58.026
hundreds of dates,

20:58.058 --> 20:59.594
our splinters,

20:59.626 --> 21:03.498
and among them,
the origin of the plague.

21:03.942 --> 21:07.068
Even for a mad hatter,
that doesn't make sense.

21:07.100 --> 21:10.190
Wh... why a thousand dates
when you only need one?

21:10.238 --> 21:12.628
You don't gift-wrap
a needle with a haystack.

21:12.669 --> 21:15.372
But the Primaries built a machine.

21:15.406 --> 21:18.542
That you needed a machine to get to.

21:18.576 --> 21:21.945
Unless it wasn't about the machine

21:21.979 --> 21:24.957
but about its function.

21:25.182 --> 21:26.746
Maybe...

21:27.008 --> 21:29.277
it was...

21:29.378 --> 21:31.875
maybe it was never meant...

21:32.074 --> 21:34.304
meant... [stammering]

21:36.127 --> 21:39.563
[engine whooshing]

21:39.597 --> 21:41.633
<i>[tense music]</i>

21:41.665 --> 21:44.636
[baby crying]

21:44.668 --> 21:47.338
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:47.370 --> 21:51.108
[indistinct chatter]

21:51.142 --> 21:58.650
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:02.086 --> 22:03.865
Cole...

22:04.088 --> 22:07.587
there was a time we made
a promise to these people.

22:08.125 --> 22:09.093
[exhales]

22:09.117 --> 22:11.087
Just remember what you told me,

22:11.261 --> 22:14.065
over and over again,
before we even met...

22:14.098 --> 22:15.133
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:15.165 --> 22:17.268
Sometimes terrible things happen...

22:17.300 --> 22:20.471
BOTH: So that great things
can happen next.

22:20.503 --> 22:23.273
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:23.307 --> 22:24.575
All this time...

22:24.608 --> 22:27.412
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:27.444 --> 22:30.314
It was always us.

22:30.348 --> 22:33.216
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

22:33.250 --> 22:40.992
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:42.393 --> 22:45.363
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

22:45.396 --> 22:48.966
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:52.610 --> 22:53.611
Okay.

22:53.636 --> 22:55.540
It's okay, Jonesy.

22:55.572 --> 22:57.341
It's okay.

22:57.375 --> 23:00.144
<i>[slow, soft music]</i>

23:00.176 --> 23:03.647
I need to see this to the end.

23:03.681 --> 23:05.683
I have to.

23:05.715 --> 23:07.484
<i>[soft string music]</i>

23:07.518 --> 23:10.021
You will.

23:10.053 --> 23:12.322
I'm here.

23:12.393 --> 23:15.396
I'll push you until the clocks stop

23:15.509 --> 23:17.678
and the road runs out.

23:17.711 --> 23:24.752
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:26.785 --> 23:31.394
I did my damnedest to enter
every coordinate, every date,

23:31.449 --> 23:34.756
but it's little more
than a jumble of data.

23:34.811 --> 23:36.380
Okay...

23:36.413 --> 23:40.384
a weapon to destroy the demon...

23:40.417 --> 23:43.271
But how would you do that exactly?

23:43.587 --> 23:46.924
The loops and tangles of time.

23:47.215 --> 23:49.884
To stop something that never started,

23:49.935 --> 23:53.244
to end something that never began,

23:53.479 --> 23:55.999
you must break them.

23:56.032 --> 23:58.133
Untangle...

23:58.158 --> 23:59.470
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:59.503 --> 24:01.746
Dr. Adler, run a simulation:

24:01.792 --> 24:04.166
the Primary code against
the current time stream.

24:04.191 --> 24:05.662
<i>[musical thrumming]</i>

24:05.687 --> 24:08.657
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

24:08.682 --> 24:15.890
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:20.336 --> 24:23.306
<i>[tense music]</i>

24:23.338 --> 24:25.173
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:25.206 --> 24:26.742
<i>This is a simulation</i>

24:26.776 --> 24:28.878
of the current time stream
as we know it.

24:28.911 --> 24:32.444
When we initiate
the Primary code sequence...

24:32.469 --> 24:33.816
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:33.848 --> 24:35.150
[beeping, chirping]

24:35.183 --> 24:37.720
- The serpent's free!
- Yeah.

24:37.752 --> 24:39.856
Only traveling in one direction again.

24:39.888 --> 24:43.202
The loops are broken, erased.

24:43.890 --> 24:47.349
Julian, show me those
splinter coordinates again.

24:47.513 --> 24:54.687
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:02.345 --> 25:03.712
[screaming]

25:03.746 --> 25:05.782
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:05.815 --> 25:07.507
<i>You were right, Katarina.</i>

25:07.538 --> 25:11.186
These dates do not represent
all our splinters.

25:11.220 --> 25:13.623
No, only Mr. Cole's.

25:13.655 --> 25:20.096
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:20.997 --> 25:24.133
<i>[intense percussive music]</i>

25:24.165 --> 25:26.258
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:26.283 --> 25:28.735
This is every time he has traveled,

25:28.804 --> 25:31.768
every moment he has affected
the time stream.

25:31.874 --> 25:36.179
- It's his entire life.
<i>- [tense music]</i>

25:36.620 --> 25:39.715
This was never about splintering.

25:39.749 --> 25:41.250
<i>[music builds]</i>

25:41.282 --> 25:42.885
<i>[tense music]</i>

25:42.917 --> 25:45.253
Let me do this for you.

25:45.287 --> 25:47.356
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:47.390 --> 25:50.627
<i>This was designed to destroy a Djinn,</i>

25:50.660 --> 25:54.864
<i>and a Djinn cannot be deleted
from just one moment.</i>

25:54.896 --> 25:58.800
It has to be removed from every moment.

25:58.834 --> 26:01.938
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:01.971 --> 26:05.323
The Primaries built a machine

26:06.109 --> 26:09.079
to erase James Cole.

26:09.127 --> 26:10.313
<i>[music swells]</i>

26:10.346 --> 26:13.316
<i>[tense music]</i>

26:13.348 --> 26:16.284
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:16.798 --> 26:18.835
No. Cole can't be a Djinn.

26:18.860 --> 26:20.585
You said yourself, this is something

26:20.610 --> 26:22.680
that can only be born of time travel.

26:22.705 --> 26:24.254
Cole's father wasn't a traveler.

26:24.326 --> 26:26.162
His mother, Marion.

26:26.194 --> 26:29.432
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:29.464 --> 26:31.067
[gun clicks]

26:31.099 --> 26:34.236
<i>[low ambient music]</i>

26:34.269 --> 26:40.843
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:40.875 --> 26:42.212
[gunshot]

26:44.814 --> 26:46.282
Hannah...

26:46.315 --> 26:49.385
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:49.417 --> 26:51.154
- [gunshot]
- [groans]

26:51.186 --> 26:52.320
No!

26:52.354 --> 26:53.890
[gasping]

26:53.923 --> 26:55.857
- Hey...
- Hey.

26:55.891 --> 26:57.960
[people screaming]

26:57.992 --> 27:00.328
- [gunshot]
- [grunts]

27:00.362 --> 27:03.332
<i>[eerie music]</i>

27:03.365 --> 27:08.136
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:08.170 --> 27:11.841
[people screaming, alarm blaring]

27:11.874 --> 27:15.377
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:15.411 --> 27:18.189
Hey... it's okay.

27:18.260 --> 27:21.955
[gasping] It's okay.

27:22.050 --> 27:24.352
This was my choice.

27:24.385 --> 27:25.954
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:25.988 --> 27:28.271
This was all I could do:

27:28.529 --> 27:30.630
be here...

27:30.859 --> 27:33.732
protect you one last time. [gasps]

27:34.263 --> 27:36.983
<i>Mothers die for their children.</i>

27:37.165 --> 27:39.434
Yours died protecting you.

27:39.468 --> 27:41.938
<i>[voice echoes]</i>

27:42.006 --> 27:44.373
<i>[echoing] So she left...</i>

27:44.405 --> 27:45.774
<i>[echoing] No.</i>

27:46.358 --> 27:48.376
The story's not over yet, James.

27:48.434 --> 27:49.879
<i>[echoing]</i>

27:49.912 --> 27:51.981
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:52.051 --> 27:57.252
I never wanted any of this for you.

27:57.286 --> 28:04.160
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:04.192 --> 28:06.194
[gasping]

28:07.574 --> 28:10.032
Hannah, hey...

28:10.065 --> 28:14.403
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:14.435 --> 28:17.405
[alarm blaring]

28:17.439 --> 28:19.008
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:19.040 --> 28:22.544
[people screaming, alarm blaring]

28:22.577 --> 28:28.384
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:28.416 --> 28:30.552
<i>[echoing] Before the day is done,</i>

28:30.586 --> 28:35.119
I imagine you'll understand,

28:35.257 --> 28:38.330
<i>that without time's will,</i>

28:38.560 --> 28:41.158
its shackles,

28:41.336 --> 28:45.236
there is the after of a Red Forest...

28:45.334 --> 28:47.036
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:47.068 --> 28:52.092
<i>Where one never has to choose anything</i>

28:52.208 --> 28:55.311
<i>over the ones they love.</i>

28:55.344 --> 28:59.315
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:59.347 --> 29:01.049
That's unfair.

29:01.083 --> 29:05.054
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:05.087 --> 29:07.056
You know, time is cruel.

29:07.088 --> 29:09.858
<i>[soft music]</i>

29:09.892 --> 29:12.528
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:12.560 --> 29:15.959
<i>You know, I watched the ones I love die,</i>

29:16.164 --> 29:19.166
<i>- defeated by time.</i>
- [muffled gunshot]

29:19.635 --> 29:21.237
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:21.269 --> 29:23.482
<i>In the end, we all lose...</i>

29:23.507 --> 29:25.073
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:25.113 --> 29:27.093
Yet you may yet win...

29:27.175 --> 29:29.345
if you choose to.

29:29.377 --> 29:33.582
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:33.615 --> 29:35.483
Good-bye, Cassandra.

29:35.517 --> 29:38.487
<i>[solemn music]</i>

29:38.519 --> 29:41.490
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:41.522 --> 29:44.159
<i>[harrowing music]</i>

29:44.192 --> 29:51.401
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:09.084 --> 30:16.292
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:31.173 --> 30:33.608
[glass shatters]

30:33.642 --> 30:36.312
<i>[shards pinging]</i>

30:43.367 --> 30:44.801
<i>"Dear, James"...</i>

30:44.835 --> 30:47.538
<i>[soft string music]</i>

30:47.578 --> 30:50.053
<i>"I'm not sure
if you'll ever find this"...</i>

30:50.078 --> 30:52.009
[machine whirs, rattles]

30:52.041 --> 30:54.611
[rumbling]

30:54.645 --> 30:57.682
<i>"If there will come a time
when you need the truth."</i>

30:57.714 --> 31:04.722
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:20.870 --> 31:28.079
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:38.254 --> 31:41.925
<i>"Perhaps someday, I will have
the chance to tell you myself."</i>

31:41.958 --> 31:49.166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:50.634 --> 31:53.365
<i>"But however you hear the tale,</i>

31:54.605 --> 31:57.141
<i>I want you to be
certain of one thing"...</i>

31:57.174 --> 31:59.644
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:59.676 --> 32:01.537
<i>"It was...</i>

32:02.432 --> 32:04.468
<i>"is...</i>

32:04.627 --> 32:06.562
<i>a love story."</i>

32:06.649 --> 32:08.218
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:08.252 --> 32:11.222
<i>[warm, gentle music]</i>

32:11.254 --> 32:15.191
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:15.224 --> 32:17.627
You all right?

32:17.660 --> 32:23.934
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:23.967 --> 32:26.937
<i>[ominous music]</i>

32:26.971 --> 32:32.108
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:32.142 --> 32:33.611
Hey, hold on!

32:33.644 --> 32:35.146
- Help me get her in the truck.
- Okay.

32:35.178 --> 32:36.840
<i>"The first time I met your father</i>

32:36.865 --> 32:38.982
<i>"was an act of bravery:</i>

32:39.082 --> 32:41.592
<i>a good man risking all
and asking nothing"...</i>

32:41.623 --> 32:44.357
You're okay. Breathe.
Look at me. Be calm.

32:44.427 --> 32:46.228
<i>"Fighting to save
the life of a stranger."</i>

32:46.253 --> 32:47.958
[engine turns over]

32:47.992 --> 32:49.659
<i>[solemn music]</i>

32:49.693 --> 32:51.228
[engine revs]

32:51.261 --> 32:54.831
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:55.005 --> 32:57.891
<i>"He reminded me of you,</i>

32:58.202 --> 33:00.171
<i>of the man you would become."</i>

33:00.204 --> 33:02.212
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:02.275 --> 33:04.312
<i>"If for a moment,</i>

33:04.412 --> 33:06.279
<i>the future taught me anything"...</i>

33:06.312 --> 33:07.881
<i>[soft piano music]</i>

33:07.915 --> 33:10.118
<i>"It was the peace of a simple life"...</i>

33:10.150 --> 33:17.324
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:18.292 --> 33:20.962
<i>"Of hunting, fishing"...</i>

33:20.995 --> 33:22.830
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:22.862 --> 33:25.932
<i>"Of quiet moments away from the world."</i>

33:25.966 --> 33:27.502
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:27.534 --> 33:29.437
<i>"He lived like I was raised."</i>

33:29.469 --> 33:31.505
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:31.539 --> 33:34.408
<i>"I knew your father
before I ever knew his name."</i>

33:34.440 --> 33:37.310
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:37.343 --> 33:40.313
<i>[solemn music]</i>

33:40.347 --> 33:42.216
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:42.248 --> 33:45.218
[truck pulling in]

33:45.252 --> 33:52.427
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:54.160 --> 33:57.130
<i>[poignant music]</i>

33:57.164 --> 33:59.000
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:59.033 --> 34:01.232
She didn't make it.

34:01.302 --> 34:03.103
I'm sorry.

34:03.137 --> 34:04.539
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:04.572 --> 34:07.073
She kept calling for you.

34:07.106 --> 34:08.408
Marion, right?

34:08.440 --> 34:10.945
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:10.976 --> 34:12.146
I'm Matthew.

34:12.178 --> 34:15.148
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:15.181 --> 34:17.150
<i>"Why did I stay?"</i>

34:17.184 --> 34:19.954
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:19.985 --> 34:22.255
<i>"To protect him, should they ever come?"</i>

34:22.289 --> 34:25.324
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:25.358 --> 34:27.228
<i>"Or was it because,</i>

34:27.293 --> 34:31.884
<i>"for all my mother's talk
of causality and eventuality,</i>

34:32.166 --> 34:35.947
<i>I'd finally found something
that felt like fate?"</i>

34:36.070 --> 34:43.275
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:43.309 --> 34:45.911
<i>"Every day, I thought about leaving"...</i>

34:45.945 --> 34:49.081
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:49.114 --> 34:52.320
<i>"And every day,
he gave me a reason to stay."</i>

34:52.351 --> 34:59.526
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:03.264 --> 35:05.198
Teach me.

35:05.231 --> 35:06.934
[chuckles]

35:06.966 --> 35:08.269
[chuckles]

35:08.302 --> 35:11.872
Yeah... she's a stubborn one.

35:11.905 --> 35:14.041
She?

35:14.073 --> 35:17.772
A car like this,
it gets you where you're going,

35:18.044 --> 35:19.944
points you straight,

35:20.120 --> 35:22.803
kicks back when you hit the wrong gear.

35:22.866 --> 35:25.086
- [chuckles]
- She's definitely a woman.

35:25.119 --> 35:28.018
I just can't get her running.

35:28.254 --> 35:30.167
Well, my father used to say,

35:30.229 --> 35:33.925
"The common core of all great
achievement is failure."

35:34.193 --> 35:36.022
I like that.

35:36.558 --> 35:38.094
Fancy way of saying,

35:38.132 --> 35:41.401
"The only failure is giving up."

35:41.434 --> 35:43.536
[chuckles softly]

35:43.570 --> 35:46.307
Will you hold that in place right there?

35:46.340 --> 35:48.910
Let me get in here with this.

35:48.943 --> 35:52.312
<i>"He was kind, honest.</i>

35:52.345 --> 35:54.347
<i>He made me laugh."</i> [giggles]

35:54.381 --> 35:56.017
<i>[soft piano music]</i>

35:56.050 --> 35:57.946
<i>"I knew we would never
grow old together,</i>

35:58.008 --> 35:59.552
<i>but I loved him anyway."</i>

35:59.586 --> 36:02.555
[fire crackling]

36:02.588 --> 36:09.997
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:22.041 --> 36:24.577
<i>"Timeless and without hesitation."</i>

36:24.611 --> 36:27.581
<i>[warm string music]</i>

36:27.613 --> 36:34.254
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:34.287 --> 36:36.056
[engine turns over]

36:36.090 --> 36:38.693
[engine revs]

36:38.726 --> 36:42.062
<i>[cheerful piano music]</i>

36:42.095 --> 36:49.137
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:52.706 --> 36:55.175
<i>"I wanted it to last"...</i>

36:55.209 --> 36:56.510
<i>[soft string music]</i>

36:56.543 --> 36:59.046
<i>"But I knew I couldn't stay"...</i>

36:59.079 --> 37:01.548
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:01.582 --> 37:03.409
<i>"For him...</i>

37:03.617 --> 37:05.285
<i>for you"...</i>

37:05.318 --> 37:06.686
[engine humming]

37:06.712 --> 37:09.449
<i>"For all those we've yet to save."</i>

37:09.490 --> 37:16.664
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:35.314 --> 37:38.177
<i>"I told you this was a love story,</i>

37:38.485 --> 37:40.851
<i>"and it is.</i>

37:41.703 --> 37:43.726
<i>Not just of a woman for a man"...</i>

37:43.757 --> 37:46.394
[distressed breathing]

37:46.427 --> 37:49.229
<i>"But a father for his son."</i>

37:49.262 --> 37:51.765
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:51.798 --> 37:53.294
<i>"This letter, James,</i>

37:53.359 --> 37:55.673
<i>"is the last story
I have left to tell you.</i>

37:57.137 --> 37:59.240
<i>The first, I think you know."</i>

37:59.273 --> 38:00.673
[sighs]

38:00.707 --> 38:05.212
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:05.244 --> 38:07.380
<i>"Thank you, James.</i>

38:07.414 --> 38:10.251
<i>"You saved my life when I was a child.</i>

38:10.283 --> 38:12.619
<i>You saved my soul when you were born."</i>

38:12.653 --> 38:14.388
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:14.421 --> 38:17.258
<i>"I was, in my life,
proud to be a Daughter"...</i>

38:17.291 --> 38:19.626
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:19.660 --> 38:22.263
<i>"But proudest to be your mother."</i>

38:22.296 --> 38:29.303
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:32.707 --> 38:35.543
<i>[dark tones, high-pitched ringing]</i>

38:35.575 --> 38:38.711
<i>[distant siren wailing]</i>

38:38.744 --> 38:41.782
[fire crackling]

39:05.539 --> 39:07.708
We had to tell you.

39:08.984 --> 39:11.252
That should be your choice.

39:19.160 --> 39:22.082
For years, I was by myself,

39:22.330 --> 39:24.600
but I was never alone.

39:26.693 --> 39:30.331
I saw you once, sitting in the park,

39:30.490 --> 39:33.974
looking down at
the luckiest little girl.

39:34.375 --> 39:37.307
The way you looked at me,

39:38.212 --> 39:40.248
the way you're looking at me now...

39:40.281 --> 39:42.917
<i>[soft string music]</i>

39:43.471 --> 39:47.717
And I wondered how anyone could
ever love anything that much.

39:48.056 --> 39:50.525
[chuckles]

39:50.558 --> 39:52.494
And I saw you.

39:52.527 --> 39:54.596
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:54.629 --> 39:58.223
I was there when you lost your father.

39:58.667 --> 40:01.603
And I was there when you
found your brother.

40:01.636 --> 40:04.640
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:05.012 --> 40:08.910
I'll be there at the end,
at the airport.

40:08.944 --> 40:14.082
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:14.114 --> 40:17.319
I can't bear to say good-bye...

40:18.353 --> 40:20.634
Because when we do...

40:21.623 --> 40:25.294
this moment between the three of us...

40:25.326 --> 40:29.997
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:30.031 --> 40:32.701
[sighs]

40:32.734 --> 40:35.103
It will be over.

40:35.136 --> 40:40.007
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:40.040 --> 40:42.372
So, maybe...

40:42.856 --> 40:44.939
one minute more?

40:45.013 --> 40:52.187
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:54.723 --> 40:56.558
There's still time.

40:56.591 --> 40:59.694
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:59.728 --> 41:02.064
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:02.096 --> 41:06.167
[thunder rumbling]

41:06.201 --> 41:08.971
[thunder crashing]

41:09.004 --> 41:13.674
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:13.707 --> 41:16.677
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:16.710 --> 41:23.953
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:26.187 --> 41:27.322
[electrical blasts]

41:27.355 --> 41:34.563
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:38.758 --> 41:42.595
[thunder rumbling]

41:47.254 --> 41:49.026
I'm the demon.

41:49.152 --> 41:52.122
<i>[ominous music]</i>

